  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-02 22:56 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] HL live trader now signs with the funded wallet\n\n**Task:** Repair the HL live-trader wallet blocker by aligning the Python live execution engine with the funded Hyperliquid wallet used by the operational `brainKID/trading/hl.js` CLI.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P3**.\n- `hl_live_trader.py` was signing with `POLYMARKET_PRIVATE_KEY` and hardcoding wallet `0x51F290588E0fB3107D9cde00984fA16f3dDA3191`.\n- The canonical HL CLI derives its wallet from `/home/ubuntu/clawd/brainKID/.evm-seed` and reports address `0x4Bf93279060fB5f71D40Ee7165D9f17535b0a2ba`, balance `37.391639`, and no open positions.\n- Pre-fix telemetry was correctly `wallet_blocked`: configured wallet `$0.00`, reference wallet `$37.39`, `misaligned=true`.\n- I patched `/home/ubuntu/clawd/hyperliquid-trader/hl_live_trader.py` to prefer `HYPERLIQUID_SEED_PATH` (default `/home/ubuntu/clawd/brainKID/.evm-seed`), derive the signing account from mnemonic, fall back to private keys only if no seed exists, and set `WALLET` from the derived signer instead of a hardcoded stale address.\n- Validation passed:\n  - `python3 -m py_compile /home/ubuntu/clawd/hyperliquid-trader/hl_live_trader.py` \u2705\n  - dry import resolved `0x4Bf93279060fB5f71D40Ee7165D9f17535b0a2ba` via `mnemonic` \u2705\n  - restarted only `hl-bot` \u2705\n  - post-restart `hl_live_state.json` now shows `status=live`, `balance=37.391639`, `wallet_blocked=false`, `misaligned=false` \u2705\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p3-hl-funded-wallet-routing-2026-05-02-2256.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** HL was not down as a process; it was live but pointed at an unfunded signer. That is worse than a crash because it looks healthy while never trading. The fix is to make the active engine use the same funded signing path as the working HL CLI, while keeping an env override for future migration.\n\n**Decision:** Make `/home/ubuntu/clawd/brainKID/.evm-seed` the default HL live-trader signing source. Keep the `$10` min balance floor. Do not open any new HL position during repair; this was infrastructure alignment only.\n\n**Next:** On the next P3 pass, inspect the first funded-wallet live cycles and verify signal generation / order gating with `$37.39` capital. If signals appear, enforce conservative notional sizing before allowing any new HL position.\n\n## 2026-05-02 22:46 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] I added alpha-context attribution to future PM outcome rows\n\n**Task:** Test whether active price-band buckets can be joined to P4 fast-regime / transition posture, and if not, close the instrumentation gap for future realized PM outcomes.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P2**.\n- I attempted to join active-hour + `v5a_pass=true` realized outcomes against `research/alpha-signals-history.jsonl` by timestamp.\n- The join found **17 active-hour V5a rows**, but",
